**janzer_beats_threshold Theorem:**

For ε > 0 with ε < 1/6:
∃ bipartite G: G not 2-degenerate ∧ ex(n;G) ≪ n^{3/2}

**Proof:**
1. Apply Janzer's counterexample with ε
2. Get 3-regular bipartite H with ex ≪ n^{4/3+ε}
3. H is not 2-degenerate (by regular3_not_2degenerate)
4. Since 4/3 + ε < 3/2 when ε < 1/6, apply asymp_trans_exponent
5. Thus ex(n;H) ≪ n^{3/2}
